properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 5 at 12:33AM MST until February 6 at 2:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS EXPECTED IN THE WIND PRONE AREAS OF SOUTHEAST
WYOMING ALONG WITH PERIODS OF BLOWING SNOW...

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 60 MPH likely,
along with areas of blowing snow.

* WHERE...Interstate 80 between Rawlins and Laramie, especially
near Arlington and Elk Mountain.

* WHEN...Now until 2 PM MST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. There will be a high blow
over risk for light, high profile vehicles including camping and
tractor trailers. In addition, areas of blowing snow may result
in significantly reduced visibilities at times.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of
58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM MST THURSDAY
